<!-- WHAT TO EXPECT -->
<section class="section-alt" id="what-to-expect">
<div class="container">
  <div style="text-align:center">
    <div class="slabel">Your Journey</div>
    <h2 class="stitle">What to Expect at Your Consultation</h2>
    <p class="ssub" style="margin:0 auto">Your first consultation with Mr Hussain is a thorough, unhurried appointment designed to give you a clear picture of your condition and all available options.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="expect-steps">
    <div class="expect-step">
      <div class="step-num">1</div>
      <h4>Referral &amp; Booking</h4>
      <p>You can self-refer or be referred by your GP. Contact Wendy to book. A referral letter is helpful but not always required.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="expect-step">
      <div class="step-num">2</div>
      <h4>History &amp; Examination</h4>
      <p>Mr Hussain will take a full history of your symptoms, their onset and impact on your daily life, followed by a clinical examination.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="expect-step">
      <div class="step-num">3</div>
      <h4>Imaging Review</h4>
      <p>X-rays or scans will be reviewed. If you do not already have imaging, arrangements will be made at or before your appointment.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="expect-step">
      <div class="step-num">4</div>
      <h4>Personalised Plan</h4>
      <p>You will leave with a clear diagnosis, a full understanding of your options, and a treatment plan tailored to your goals and lifestyle.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid #e2e0db;border-radius:10px;padding:28px 32px;margin-top:40px;max-width:760px;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto">
    <p style="font-size:.9rem;color:#5a5a5a;line-height:1.8;margin:0"><strong style="color:#0c1f3f">What to bring:</strong> Any previous X-rays, MRI scans or reports, a list of current medications, your insurance details (if applicable), and any referral letter from your GP. Wear comfortable clothing that allows easy access to your hip or knee.</p>
  </div>
</div>
</section>

<!-- INSURANCE & FEES -->
<section class="section" id="insurance">
<div class="container">
  <div style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:8px">
    <div class="slabel">Paying for Your Care</div>
    <h2 class="stitle">Insurance &amp; Self-Pay</h2>
    <p class="ssub" style="margin:0 auto">Mr Hussain accepts all major private health insurance policies and welcomes self-paying patients. Transparent fee information is available before any commitment is made.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="ins-grid">
    <div class="ins-card">
      <h3>
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/></svg>
        Private Health Insurance
      </h3>
      <p>Mr Hussain is recognised by all major UK private health insurers. Please have your policy number and pre-authorisation reference to hand when booking.</p>
      <ul class="ins-list">
        <li>Bupa</li>
        <li>AXA Health</li>
        <li>Vitality Health</li>
        <li>WPA</li>
        <li>Aviva</li>
        <li>Cigna, Allianz &amp; most others</li>
      </ul>
      <p style="font-size:1rem;color:#999;margin-top:16px;margin-bottom:0">If you are unsure whether your insurer covers Mr Hussain, contact Wendy and she will verify this for you.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ins-card">
      <h3>
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12" y2="12"/><line x1="12" y1="16" x2="12.01" y2="16"/></svg>
        Self-Pay (No Insurance)
      </h3>
      <p>Self-paying patients are very welcome. Consultation fees at The Harborne Hospital (HCA) are as follows. Fees at The Woodlands Suite and The Priory vary — please contact Wendy for a quote.</p>
      <div class="ins-fee">
        <div class="fee-badge">
          <div class="fee-amt">&pound;250</div>
          <div class="fee-label">New Consultation</div>
        </div>
        <div class="fee-badge">
          <div class="fee-amt">&pound;175</div>
          <div class="fee-label">Follow-Up</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p style="font-size:1rem;color:#999;margin-top:16px;margin-bottom:0">Surgical fees and hospital facility costs are separate and will be clearly outlined before any procedure is agreed.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
</section>

<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="section-alt" id="faq">
<div class="container">
  <div style="text-align:center">
    <div class="slabel">Common Questions</div>
    <h2 class="stitle">Booking FAQs</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="faq-list">

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q">Do I need a GP referral to see Mr Hussain? <span>+</span></div>
      <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">You can self-refer as a private patient — a GP referral is not always required. However, a referral letter is helpful as it provides Mr Hussain with your relevant medical history and investigation results. If you do not have a referral, please mention this when contacting Wendy and she will advise accordingly.</div></div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q">How quickly can I get an appointment? <span>+</span></div>
      <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Mr Hussain is currently accepting new patients and appointments are usually available within a few weeks. Wendy will advise on the earliest available slot at your preferred hospital when you contact her.</div></div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q">Which hospital should I choose? <span>+</span></div>
      <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">All three hospitals offer excellent facilities. Your choice may depend on your insurer's approved hospital list, your location, or your preference for a particular hospital's environment. Wendy can advise which hospitals are covered by your insurer and help you find the most convenient option.</div></div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q">Will my insurer cover the consultation fee? <span>+</span></div>
      <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Most private health insurers cover consultation fees once you have pre-authorisation. Please contact your insurer before booking to obtain authorisation and a reference number. If you are unsure, Wendy can help you confirm your cover.</div></div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q">Can I have a video or telephone consultation? <span>+</span></div>
      <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">In some circumstances a video consultation may be appropriate, for example for an initial discussion or follow-up review. However, for a first assessment involving examination and imaging review, an in-person appointment is strongly recommended. Please mention your preference when contacting Wendy.</div></div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q">How long will the consultation take? <span>+</span></div>
      <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">A new patient consultation with Mr Hussain typically lasts 30 to 45 minutes. This allows sufficient time for a thorough history, examination, imaging review, and a full discussion of your options. Please allow extra time for any pre-appointment paperwork or imaging at the hospital.</div></div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="faq-q">What happens after my consultation? <span>+</span></div>
      <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Following your consultation, Mr Hussain will write to your GP with a summary of findings and recommendations. If surgery is recommended, Wendy will guide you through the next steps including pre-operative assessment and scheduling. There is never any pressure to proceed — the decision is entirely yours.</div></div>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>
</section>

